```

First you get a map of customer ids and (Wrapped in an `Optional` due to the way `Collectors.maxBy()` works) the most recent order by date. Then filter out the entries where that most recent date is within the last six months. Then extract the remaining orders from the `Optional`s and return them in a `List`. If you just want the customer IDs and don&#39;t care about the rest of the `Order` object, modify the final `map()` and returned type appropriately.

